text: Kaare Sparby (25 June 1904 – 23 October 2001) was a Norwegian politician for the Conservative Party. He served as a deputy representative to the Norwegian Parliament from Hedmark during the term 1945-1949\. He was an engineer by profession. ==References== * Category:1904 births Category:2001 deaths Category:Conservative Party (Norway) politicians Category:Deputy members of the Storting Category:Hedmark politicians
